The paper deals with detecting action units (AUs) on human faces using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and expert prior knowledge. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the integration of various dynamic models, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed approach on two datasets, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
